France Wants ECB to Help Leverage Bailout Fund, Official Says

-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-10-13T09:51:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/france-wants-ecb-to-help-leverage-bailout-fund-official-says.html
France  wants the  European Central
Bank  to help boost the firepower of the European Financial
Stability Facility through leverage, a government official told
reporters today. In the same briefing, he said partial
government bond guarantees could encourage investors and reduce
borrowing costs.  The ECB has opposed helping leverage the bailout fund.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Deen in Paris at 
 markdeen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  